 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Fully Networked Command, Control, and Communications (FNC3) Subject Matter Expert JHNA, Inc. Alexandria, VA Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Overview:
 
JHNA is seeking a Fully Networked Command, Control and Communications (FNC3) Subject Matter Expert with experience and expertise in cutting edge technologies and integration of these technologies into new and innovative warfighting capabilities. 
The mission of OUSD (R&E) as the Chief Technology Officer is to foster technological dominance across the Department of Defense and ensure the advantage of the American warfighter. The OUSD (R&E) enterprise is composed of the Directorate of Defense Research and Engineering for Advanced Capabilities; the Directorate of Defense Research and Engineering for Research and Technology; the Directorate of Defense Research and Engineering for Modernization which provides strategic direction for the 11 modernization priority areas (Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning, Autonomy, Biotechnology, Cyber, Directed Energy, Fully Networked Command, Control & Communications, Hypersonics, Microelectronics, Space, Quantum Science, and 5G Network Technology). 
Come join a certified Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business (SDVOSB) that is focused on providing a broad range of services that help make us "The Warfighter to Engineer Interface". Our services include Mission Engineering, System Engineering and DT&E in such development phases as: Planning, execution, and assessment of Developmental or Operational Test & Evaluation; Technology evaluation and prioritization; and Operational and System DoDAF View (OVs, SVs). JHNA offers highly competitive benefit packages and a culture that fosters teamwork and collaboration all while supporting our Warfighter! 
Responsibilities:
 Support the PD participation in the Joint All-Domain Command & Control Cross Functional Team (JADC2 CFT) and the C3 Leadership Board 
Demonstrate in-depth technical knowledge and experience with existing and future advanced DoD weapon systems and their capabilities, concept of operations, limitations, and upgrade capacities 
Utilize experience and expertise in cutting edge technologies and application of technologies into new and innovative warfighting capabilities. 
Analyzing new or proposed policies or regulations to assess impact on DoD developing and/or fielding of future FNC3 systems 
Develop classified and proprietary appendices that build on existing assessments and evaluation activities of the U.S. manufacturing and defense industrial base and supply chains as well as anticipated timelines for adversaries to develop similar or countering capabilities 
Experience in semantic technologies for specifying meaning of information carried in the protocols 
Able to interact effectively with experimental teams implementing early prototypes, contributing to experiment design to maximize benefits for Universal Command and Control (UC2) technical design, and use lessons learned to improve the standard 
Communicate UC2 vision and progress effectively in a wide range of private and public venues 
Understand DoD technology development and systems acquisition processes 
Set schedules and milestones for standards development and version releases, balancing technical and user needs 
Qualifications:
 
REQUIRED EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS 
7+ years of FNC3 program experience 
Master's Degree in a STEM field field +14 years of experience 
Active DoD issued TS with SCI eligibility within the last 12 months 
Experience in developing and demonstrating mission base capabilities to fill persistent gaps within the National Defense Strategy (NDS). 
Previous experience with Department of Defense RDT&E mission and processes 
Previous experience in engineering, analysis of alternatives, integration, requirements, and testing 
Experience with Cross-Domain Solutions 
Excellent writing, communication and briefing skills 
DESIRED EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS 
War College Experience 
Acquisition Experience 
Experience working in Joint Staff, with the DoD Labs, and DARPA 
